<p><strong>Stage 1 — Attract.</strong> A piece of content — a blog post, a YouTube video, a paid ad, a webinar invitation — draws a potential customer into your orbit. Their first touchpoint is not a sales pitch; it is useful, relevant content that addresses a problem they are already trying to solve. This stage is pure value delivery.</p>

<p><strong>Stage 2 — Capture.</strong> A landing page, a pop-up form, or an event registration page exchanges something of value — a how-to guide, a tool, a webinar seat, a discount code — for contact information. This is where a visitor becomes a lead. The exchange must feel worth it to the prospect.</p>

<p><strong>Stage 3 — Qualify.</strong> Marketing automation software scores the lead based on demographic fit (job title, company size, geography) and behavioral signals (pages visited, emails opened, content downloaded). High-scoring leads become MQLs and are escalated for further attention. Low-scoring leads continue in nurture.</p>

<p><strong>Stage 4 — Nurture.</strong> Email sequences, retargeting ads, and personal outreach build the relationship over time until the prospect is ready to have a sales conversation or make a direct purchase.</p>

<p>A practical example: a small business owner searches "how to get more customers from Facebook," finds a blog post, downloads a free checklist in exchange for their email, receives a five-part email sequence over two weeks, and on the fifth email clicks through to book a consultation. They were a raw lead at Stage 2. They became an SQL when they requested the consultation.</p>

<p>This funnel pattern plays out across every industry. In the affiliate marketing space, <a href="https://olsp.profitandprivilege.com/reviews/olsp-academy/">OLSP Academy</a> teaches this exact framework to new marketers. Community-based platforms like <a href="https://olsp.profitandprivilege.com/reviews/olsp-community-builders/">OLSP Community Builders</a> apply a social-organic variation: attract through community engagement, capture through relationship-building, nurture through regular content and conversation. <a href="https://olsp.profitandprivilege.com/reviews/olsp-live-profit-builders/">OLSP Live Profit Builders</a> adds a live-training layer that functions as a high-intent capture event — attendees are already MQLs before they finish the session.</p>

