    <section id="faq">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions About Lead Generation</h2>

      <FaqItem question="What is a lead in marketing?" answer="A lead is a person or organization that has expressed interest in a product or service — typically by sharing their contact information through a form, a signup, or a direct inquiry. The key distinction is intent: a lead has taken an action that signals potential buying interest, separating them from an anonymous visitor who has given you no way to follow up." />

      <FaqItem question="What is the difference between inbound and outbound lead generation?" answer="Inbound lead generation attracts prospects who are already searching for solutions — through SEO, content marketing, or social media — so they discover you organically. Outbound lead generation involves reaching out to people who have not yet expressed intent: cold email, paid ads targeting cold audiences, solo ad campaigns, or direct social outreach." />

      <FaqItem question="What is an MQL versus an SQL?" answer="An MQL (Marketing Qualified Lead) is a prospect who fits your ideal customer profile and has taken meaningful engagement actions — downloading content, attending a webinar, revisiting key pages multiple times — but has not yet been evaluated by the sales team." />

      <FaqItem question="How much does lead generation cost?" answer="Cost per lead varies significantly by channel and industry. The median B2B cost per lead across all channels is approximately $213. By channel: SEO produces leads at roughly $31 each; email marketing at $53; webinars at $72; LinkedIn Ads at $75; search engine ads (PPC) at $110; trade shows and events at $811–$881 per lead." />

      <FaqItem question="What is the most effective lead generation channel?" answer="No single channel is universally most effective — the answer depends on your audience, sales cycle, and budget horizon. For long-term, low-cost volume, SEO and content marketing consistently outperform paid channels: content marketing generates 3× more leads at 62% lower cost than outbound." />

      <FaqItem question="What is lead nurturing and why does it matter?" answer="Lead nurturing is the process of building relationships with prospects who are not yet ready to buy — through email sequences, targeted content, retargeting ads, and personal outreach — until they reach purchase readiness." />

      <FaqItem question="How do you measure lead generation success?" answer="The primary lead generation metrics are: (1) Total leads generated per period; (2) Cost per lead (CPL) by channel; (3) Lead-to-MQL conversion rate; (4) MQL-to-SQL conversion rate — industry median is 9.8%; (5) SQL-to-customer conversion rate; (6) Cost per acquired customer." />

      <FaqItem question="What tools are commonly used for lead generation?" answer="Lead generation tools fall into five categories: Traffic sources (Ahrefs, Semrush, Google Ads), Landing page builders (Unbounce, Leadpages, Instapage), Email capture and marketing (OptinMonster, ConvertKit, Mailchimp), CRM and qualification (HubSpot, Salesforce, Pipedrive), and Prospecting and outreach (LeadsMiner Pro, OLSP Mineeme)." />
    </section>

